{
    "id": "electronics/thermistor-reading",
    "title": "Read a Thermistor",
    "description": "Wire a thermistor to your Arduino and log temperature values.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/basic_circuit.svg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Let's expand your sensor skills. Pair a 10 kΩ NTC thermistor with a 10 kΩ resistor for an Arduino Uno voltage divider. Work on a non-conductive surface and unplug the USB cable before wiring.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "arduino-ide-install",
                    "text": "Install the Arduino IDE"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "wire",
                    "text": "Show me."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "wire",
            "text": "With the USB cable still unplugged, place the thermistor and 10 kΩ resistor in series on the breadboard between 5 V and GND to form a voltage divider. Use jumper wires to link their junction to A0 on the Arduino Uno. Keep leads separated, verify resistor values and double-check connections before restoring power.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "monitor",
                    "text": "Circuit ready.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "72b4448e-27d9-4746-bd3a-967ff13f501b",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "d1105b87-8185-4a30-ba55-406384be169f",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "3cd82744-d2aa-414e-9f03-80024b624066",
                            "count": 3
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "fb60696a-6c94-4e5e-9277-b62377ee6d73",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
